<h1>Problem 200 - 2009 IMO, P3 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Suppose that \(s_1, s_2, s_3, \dots\) is a strictly increasing sequence of positive integers such that the subsequences \[s_{s_1}, s_{s_2}, s_{s_3}, \dots \quad \text{and} \quad s_{s_1 + 1}, s_{s_2 + 1}, s_{s_3 + 1}, \dots\] are both arithmetic progressions. Prove that the sequence \(s_1, s_2, s_3, \dots\) is itself an arithmetic progression.</p>
